## Limitations

The findings presented in this report are based on surveys and studies that may have limitations in terms of sample size, geographic coverage, and the time frame of data collection. Additionally, the emotional and psychological responses to climate change are complex and can vary widely among individuals, making it challenging to generalize findings across different populations. Furthermore, the political and cultural contexts in which these surveys were conducted can influence the results, potentially leading to biases in the data.